  "commentary": "**DEALER HEDGING COMMENTARY:**\n\nWith SPX at 6600.27 sitting right between the max negative gamma at 6590 (-16.7B) and max positive gamma at 6605 (+25.2B), dealers are in a neutral hedging stance but poised to provide strong support on any dip toward 6590 where they'll aggressively buy. The PIN regime with 30.9B total GEX suggests dealers will fade moves away from this tight range, selling any push above 6605 and buying weakness below 6600. Key inflection points are the 6590 amplifying wall below and the massive 6605/6610 stabilizing walls above—expect choppy action within this 15-point range until a decisive break.\n\n**Bottom line:** Price should bounce between 6590-6610 with dealers keeping it range-bound.",
